sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1692031
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: meffBlue blue chromoprotein with RBS and promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This plasmid contains the meffBlue blue chromoprotein gene found in the BBa_K1033902 part, with the RBS and promoter from part BBa_K608002.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jack Ryan Takahashi
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is made from parts BBa_K608002 and BBa_K1033902.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K608002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: you can insert your part behind this part so it will be immediatly expressed in e.coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Julia M??ller

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: meffBlue
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This chromoprotein from the coral Montipora efflorescens, meffBlue, naturally exhibits strong color when expressed.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Erik Gullberg
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Synthesized and codon optimized for E coli by GenScript.
